{"slide_id": "5aed46f009ac84854c5c1cebd08f867d-DASH_Presentati__s2__G1_TEXT_OVERFLOW", "width": 960, "height": 540, "elements": [{"element_id": "shp129", "type": "image", "bbox": {"x": 492.26, "y": 307.31, "width": 460.55, "height": 226.38}, "text": "", "style": {}, "z": 0, "placeholder_id": null, "metadata": {}}, {"element_id": "shp130", "type": "title", "bbox": {"x": 57.13, "y": 33.98, "width": 367.84, "height": 25.13}, "text": "Solar Ultraviolet Imager (SUVI) series", "style": {"font_size_pt": 16.0}, "z": 1, "placeholder_id": "TITLE (1)", "metadata": {"role": "TITLE (1)"}}, {"element_id": "shp131", "type": "body", "bbox": {"x": 32.81, "y": 71.57, "width": 396.19, "height": 150.25}, "text": "Vendor writes and controls the ground processing algorithm (GPA) for analyzing data between L0 -> L1 \nNCEI writes Python algorithms to generate L2 products (e.g thematic maps, flare predictions) made to run on SWPC systems\nL2 products are conceived in collaboration by NCEI/SWPC", "style": {"font_size_pt": 12.0}, "z": 2, "placeholder_id": null, "metadata": {}}, {"element_id": "shp132", "type": "body", "bbox": {"x": 483.82, "y": 73.02, "width": 443.69, "height": 213.26}, "text": "Vendor writes and delivers a starting working (IDL) pipeline for data processing from L0 -> L2, but does not process data after instrument commissioning\nNCEI/SWPC translate the pipeline to Python and run separate versions:\nSWPC / NCEI generate operational / retrospective L1 and L2 products\nMain difference lies in the data used for the background images and possibility for reprocessing to account for instrument degradation", "style": {"font_size_pt": 12.0}, "z": 3, "placeholder_id": null, "metadata": {}}, {"element_id": "shp133", "type": "body", "bbox": {"x": 9.76, "y": 4.87, "width": 598.05, "height": 21.01}, "text": "A tale of two Technical Task Agreements . . .", "style": {"font_size_pt": 13.0}, "z": 4, "placeholder_id": null, "metadata": {}}, {"element_id": "shp134", "type": "image", "bbox": {"x": 19.97, "y": 247.55, "width": 428.99, "height": 286.14}, "text": "", "style": {}, "z": 5, "placeholder_id": null, "metadata": {}}, {"element_id": "shp135", "type": "shape", "bbox": {"x": 463.85, "y": 38.63, "width": 1.26, "height": 495.06}, "text": "", "style": {}, "z": 6, "placeholder_id": null, "metadata": {}}, {"element_id": "shp136", "type": "title", "bbox": {"x": 540.51, "y": 33.98, "width": 383.18, "height": 25.13}, "text": "Compact CORonagraph (CCOR) series", "style": {"font_size_pt": 32.0}, "z": 7, "placeholder_id": "TITLE (1)", "metadata": {"role": "TITLE (1)"}}], "metadata": {"scene": "full_proposal", "source": "zenodo10k"}}